# SSH Implementation Project Rules

## Project Context
This is an educational SSH server and client implementation in Rust demonstrating all 6 phases of SSH connection establishment.

## Key Information
- Default user: testuser
- Default password: testpass
- Default port: 2222
- Keys stored in: ~/.ssh_edu/

## Common Tasks
- To run server: `cargo run -- server`
- To run client: `cargo run -- client --host localhost --port 2222 --user testuser`
- Password for testuser: testpass

## Architecture
- Phase 1: TCP Connection (server/tcp.rs, client/connection.rs)
- Phase 2: Protocol Version Exchange (protocol/version.rs)
- Phase 3: Key Exchange (protocol/key_exchange.rs, crypto/dh.rs)
- Phase 4: Server Authentication (protocol/server_auth.rs)
- Phase 5: Client Authentication (protocol/client_auth.rs)
- Phase 6: Session Establishment (protocol/session.rs, crypto/encryption.rs)

